HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 987
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate J. Clyde Edwards on
the celebration of his ninety-fifth birthday.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pay tribute to those citizens who are celebrating
special occasions in their estimable lives; and
WHEREAS, J. Clyde Edwards celebrates his ninety-fifth birthday on March 25, 2026, a
milestone commemorated as yet another precious souvenir of life's rich pageant; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Edwards has lived an amazing life and has experienced firsthand the
breadth and span of American history; and
WHEREAS, Clyde Edwards was born in Selma, Alabama, and is one of nine siblings; he
married his sweetheart, Jean, in 1950; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Edwards served in the army during the Korean War; he was deployed
on March 13, 1951, and was initially stationed in Seattle, Washington, prior to his company
moving to Japan for three weeks before finally receiving orders to serve on the front line in
Korea; and
WHEREAS, Clyde Edwards remained with his company on the front line until late
September 1952, when they were called to rest and regroup while waiting for more
reinforcements; once reinforcements arrived, they were moved to an island off the coast of
Korea to guard Korean prisoners; and
WHEREAS, in March 1953, Mr. Edwards was ordered to Fort Sill and honorably
discharged; he was recently awarded the Ambassador of Peace medal from the South Korean
government for his service; and
HJR0987
013542
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Clyde Edwards came home to Selma and started a job at Sears & Roebuck;
later that year, he and his family moved to Chattanooga, where he secured a job with Southern
Rail; and
WHEREAS, in November 1955, Mr. Edwards began working at Combustion
Engineering; through hard work and dedication, he moved his way up from drill press operator
to layout and design, to process engineering, and, ultimately, ended up as the manager of the
purchasing department, from which position he retired in 1986; and
WHEREAS, his wife passed away in February 2018; today, Clyde Edwards lives and
works on his small farm in Soddy Daisy; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Edwards especially enjoys being around people, playing with his great-
grandchildren, worshipping at his church, working on his tractor, and playing cards and bingo at
the Soddy Daisy senior center; and
WHEREAS, Clyde Edwards has been an important member of the Shriners organization
for many years; his service with the organization includes driving a bus of injured children and
their families to hospitals and volunteering at various Shriners events to hand out socks and
other items to children in need; and
WHEREAS, he is also passionate about politics; he drove tour buses for various
politicians and can be regularly found at Saturday breakfasts at local fire departments to voice
his opinion to politicians; and
WHEREAS, according to Mr. Edwards, the key to a long life is bone-in pork chops and
raisin pecan pie—his absolute favorite meal; and
WHEREAS, Clyde Edwards is a joy to be around and a blessing to all who have the
good fortune of knowing him; and
WHEREAS, as Mr. Edwards marks his ninety-fifth birthday, he remains a beloved
member of his community who is admired for his faith, integrity, and enthusiasm for life; and
- 2 - 013542

WHEREAS, we wish to grasp this golden opportunity to specially recognize one of
Tennessee's most outstanding citizens on this very special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and congratulate J. Clyde Edwards on the celebration of
his ninety-fifth birthday and extend to him our best wishes for many happy returns of the day.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
